The paper deals with the development of logic as a formal theory of computability, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the complexity of a fragment of Computability Logic, which involves computational complexity and falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the axiomatization of logics, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the extraction of computational algorithms from proofs, which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the soundness and completeness of a logic, which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
